OL,3,CIsland Energy CEO apologises for
OL,4,C'distress' caused after gas leak
OL,6,F"This is a fortunately very rare
OL,7,Foccurrence where we have to evacuate
OL,8,Fany people.
OL,10,F"There are lessons to learn from that,
OL,11,Fwe don't want things like this to
OL,12,Fhappen very often, but we could be
OL,13,Fslicker in our communication going
OL,14,Fforward.
OL,16,F"I apologise for the distress that was
OL,17,Fcaused but ultimately, I think the
OL,18,Fmost important thing was that people
OL,19,Fwere being kept safe and fortunately
OL,20,Fno one was hurt or injured."
