OL,3,CIsland Energy CEO apologises for
OL,4,C'distress' caused after gas leak
OL,6,FGraeme Millar applauded the member of
OL,7,Fthe public who reported the incident,
OL,8,Fexplaining: "(They) did what they
OL,9,Fshould do: they smelled gas and called
OL,10,Fthe emergency hotline.
OL,12,F"We very much encourage people that if
OL,13,Fthey ever feel unsafe, if they smell
OL,14,Fgas or anything else contact us (...)
OL,15,Fwe will attend immediately.
OL,17,F"On average for every six calls we get
OL,18,Fto the emergency line, only one of
OL,19,Fthem involves a gas leak, so we're
OL,20,Freally here to help."
