OL,3,CIsland Energy CEO apologises for
OL,4,C'distress' caused after gas leak
OL,6,F"I want to do what I can to serve the
OL,7,Fcommunity that I live in and make sure
OL,8,Fthat we have a safe, cost-effective,
OL,9,Freliable source of low-carbon energy
OL,10,Ffor the island."
OL,12,FThe Island Energy boss says that work
OL,13,Fhas been done to make the gas network
OL,14,Fsafer, with more upgrading into the
OL,15,Fnetwork.
OL,17,FHe explains: "We are investing a very
OL,18,Fsubstantial amount of money - over the
OL,19,Flast three years #4 million in
OL,20,Fupgrading and maintaining the gas
OL,21,Finfrastructure on the island.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/9
